'''University of Colorado Denver School of Dental Medicine''' is a school of dentistry located in the United States city of [[Aurora, Colorado|Aurora]]. The school is the only dental school in the state of [[Colorado]]. 
== History ==
University of Colorado Denver School of Dental Medicine is a part of [[University of Colorado at Denver]]. This school was established in 1973 by an amendment to the state constitution,<ref>http://www.uchsc.edu/sod/programs/overview.htm</ref> but it was not a new dental school. This school took over a private dental school that had been founded in [[1922]].

== Academics ==
University of Colorado Denver School of Dental Medicine awards following degrees:
*Doctor of Dental Surgery 
== Departments ==
University of Colorado Denver School of Dental Medicine includes the following departments:
*Department of Applied Dentistry
*Department of Craniofacial Biology 
*Department of Dental Hygiene
*Department of Diagnostic and Biological Sciences
*Department of Pediatric Dentistry
*Department of Orthodontics
*Department of Restorative Dentistry
*Department of Surgical Dentistry
*Department of Public Health
== Accreditation ==
University of Colorado Denver School of Dental Medicine is currently accredited by ADA.<ref>http://www.ada.org/prof/ed/programs/search_ddsdmd_us.asp</ref>

